      </div>
      <div class="bylaws-content">
        <div class="bylaws-intro">
          <p>Brampton regulates short-term rentals under By-law 165-2021. The city requires licensing and has specific limits on nights and bedrooms. Read our <a href="/blog/brampton-airbnb-short-term-rental-guide-2026">complete Brampton STR rules guide</a> for everything you need to operate legally.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bylaws-grid">
          <div class="bylaw-card highlight-card">
            <h3>180 Night Annual Limit</h3>
            <p>Brampton caps short-term rentals at <strong>180 nights per calendar year</strong>. This is one of the most important rules to track. We provide night tracking as part of our management service to ensure you stay compliant.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>License Required - $150/Year</h3>
            <p>All STR operators must obtain a license from the City. The annual fee is $150, and licenses must be renewed by September 30 each year. Your license number must appear on all listings.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Principal Residence Only</h3>
            <p>Short-term rentals must be your principal residence, where you normally live and receive mail. Investment properties cannot be used for STRs under 28 days. Nearby <a href="/hamilton-airbnb-management">Hamilton</a> has similar rules.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Maximum 3 Bedrooms</h3>
            <p>You can rent a maximum of 3 bedrooms individually within your STR. This limit applies regardless of your home's total bedroom count.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>$2 Million Insurance</h3>
            <p>Operators must maintain liability insurance of at least $2,000,000. Your insurance policy must specifically cover short-term rental activity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Criminal Record Check</h3>
            <p>License applications require a criminal record check. This must be submitted with your initial application and may be required for renewals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Occupancy Limits</h3>
            <p>Guest occupancy is limited to 1 person per 14 square metres of habitable floor space. This determines your maximum guest count regardless of bedroom number.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>4% Municipal Accommodation Tax</h3>
            <p>Brampton charges a 4% MAT on all short-term rentals. This is typically collected and remitted automatically by platforms like Airbnb.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
